# Project Structure and Location

## Critical Path Information

**The actual Next.js application code is located in the `/next-app/` directory, NOT in the root.**

All development commands, file operations, and navigation must account for this structure:

- Root workspace: `C:\Dev\CursorUdemy\`
- Next.js app location: `C:\Dev\CursorUdemy\next-app\`
- Source code: `C:\Dev\CursorUdemy\next-app\src\`

## File Path Guidelines

When working with project files:

**✅ CORRECT file paths:**
- `next-app/src/app/page.tsx`
- `next-app/src/components/ui/button.tsx`
- `next-app/package.json`
- `next-app/drizzle.config.ts`

**❌ INCORRECT file paths:**
- `src/app/page.tsx` (missing next-app prefix)
- `package.json` (missing next-app prefix)
- `app/page.tsx` (missing next-app/src prefix)

## Directory Navigation

When referencing directories in commands or file operations:
- Always include the `next-app/` prefix for any application-related paths
- Use relative paths from the workspace root when possible
- Remember that all npm commands, Next.js commands, and build tools operate from within the `next-app/` directory

